[SN]TITLE[SN]
Josh Yorwerth: Crawley Town sign defender on one-year deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Centre-back Josh Yorwerth has agreed a one-year deal to join Crawley following a successful loan period with the League Two club last season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Yorwerth, 21, was released by Ipswich in May and made 24 appearances for Crawley after joining in September.
The Wales under-21 international has the option to extend his contract at the Red Devils by another year.
"Josh is a player we definitely feel is capable of improving a lot," head coach Dermot Drummy said.
